data.enText: many in number; involving many different people or things

data.chText: 各种文件的大量的副本

data.enText: to suffer multiple injuries (= in many different places in the body)
a multiple birth (= several babies born to a mother at one time)
a multiple pile-up (= a crash involving many vehicles)

data.chText: 多户所有 / 使用的房屋
data.enText: a house in multiple ownership/occupancy (= owned/occupied by several different people or families)
a quantity that contains another quantity an exact number of times
8 is the lowest common multiple of 8 and 4.

data.chText: 购买旅行支票以10欧元的倍数计算面值。
data.enText: Traveller's cheques are available in multiples of €10 (= to the value of €10, €20, €30, etc.) .

tr: the product of a quantity by an integer
having or involving or consisting of more than one part or entity or individual
example: made multiple copies of the speech
his multiple achievements in public life
a pineapple is a multiple fruit

value.def: You use multiple to describe things that consist of many parts, involve many people, or have many uses.

example.ex: The most common multiple births are twins, two babies born at the same time.
example.tran: 最常见的多胎是双胞胎，两个婴儿同时出生。

value.tran: 多部分的;涉及多人的;有多种用途的

value.def: If one number is a multiple of a smaller number, it can be exactly divided by that smaller number.

example.ex: Their numerical system, derived from the Babylonians, was based on multiples of the number six.
example.tran: 他们的数制源自古巴比伦人，以数字6的倍数为基数。

value.def: A multiple or a multiple store is a shop with a lot of branches in different towns.

example.ex: It made it almost impossible for the smaller retailer to compete against the multiples.
example.tran: 这使得小零售商几乎不可能跟连锁店竞争。

trans: 编码部分多址；缩写词为CDMA
多级；多段式；多级式；多阶段
多店铺商店，联号（锁）商店
